<br>
As far as Chanter Sites, I can't remember many.  But as for class reccomendations...Don't TASH till tank has aggro...watch the timing on the mezzes.  Keep your buffs going on the group.<br>
<br>
TASH is a BIG, BIG, BIG aggro ! ! !  <br>
After you get away with tashing the mob, then try to slow or enfeeble him.  but WAIT till the Tank has agg,  most times I go w/ 80% as a guide, depending on the moband tank.<br>
<br>
Mezzing.<br>
When you mezz a mob, you hope it sticks, otherwise you hope you have a good healer..  But, after the mezz takes, try to learn how long it lasts, so you can re-mezz it b4 it breaks.  If you have multiple mezzed, tht's your job, don't debuff unless you can.  Tell your group to ROOT what they are gonna wake up, cause that mob is gonna be p'o'ed at you ! !  If there is only one add, then debuff as you can..<br>
<br>
Keep the Tanks with fresh Haste, Zing (when needed) and keep the Casters/Healers with fresh Crack.  Remind buffers to keep you w/ HP's or AC's,  there is a reason we're called PAPER CASTERS...lol<br>
<br>
Hopefully that will help for a while.<br>
<br>
